Zen Browser is a Firefox-based browser focused on privacy, performance, and
a distraction-free browsing experience. It features a customizable sidebar,
tab grouping, and a clean minimalist UI built on top of Mozilla's engine.

This port installs the official Linux binary under the FreeBSD Linux
compatibility layer (linux_base-rl9), including:

 - Stub libraries for the compat layer (libmfx, libzvbi, libsoxr, AMR codecs,
   SVT-AV1) required by the bundled FFmpeg to load successfully
 - libnotify (from Rocky Linux 9) for system notifications via DBus
 - A wrapper script that auto-detects Widevine CDM (for DRM playback) and
   configures PulseAudio, GTK theme, and DBus session automatically

DRM (Widevine) requires MOZ_DISABLE_GMP_SANDBOX=1 because FreeBSD's Linux
compat layer does not support Linux user namespaces. This is set automatically
by the wrapper script.

WWW: https://zen-browser.app
